SCHEMA: compat/endpoint_descriptor.schema
schema_id: dominium.schema.compat.endpoint_descriptor
schema_version: 1.0.0
stability: core

PURPOSE:
- Define the deterministic capability and contract descriptor emitted by an interoperating product endpoint.
- Provide the canonical input surface for capability negotiation.

NON-SEMANTICS:
- EndpointDescriptor does not mutate truth.
- EndpointDescriptor does not authorize simulation behavior by itself.

REQUIRED SHAPE:
record endpoint_descriptor
  required:
    - schema_version: tag
    - product_id: id
    - product_version: tag
    - protocol_versions_supported: [map]
    - semantic_contract_versions_supported: [map]
    - feature_capabilities: [id]
    - required_capabilities: [id]
    - optional_capabilities: [id]
    - degrade_ladders: [map]
    - deterministic_fingerprint: sha256
    - extensions: map

INVARIANTS:
- protocol_versions_supported must be deterministically ordered before hashing
- semantic_contract_versions_supported must be deterministically ordered before hashing
- capabilities are filtered through the capability registry before negotiation
- unknown capabilities are inert by default
